ZCZC EE44
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 142300 UTC
A LOW 978 LIES OVER S-E GERMAN BIGHT AT FIRST GRADUALLY MOV N INTO FISHER
BY MIDDAY TUESDAY. DPN TO 988 BY MIDDAY WEDNESDAY THEN TO 997 OVERNIGHT
WHILE MIGRATING INTO SCANDINAVIA. A SECOND LOW 989 IS CENTRED AT ROCKALL
MONDAY EVENING. THIS LOW DRIFTS S-EWARDS REACHING PLYMOUTH MIDDAY TUESDAY
THEN ENTERING FRANCE THROUGH THE NIGHT. A THIRD LOW 968 CENTRED OVER GREENLAND
EXTENDS INTO SE ICELAND THROUGH THURSDAY AFTERNOON. GALES ACROSS FITZROY
INITIALLY WITH STRG TO NEAR GALE WINDS S OF 52 N AND W OF 04 W. GALES ALSO
AFFECT SOLE AND SHANNON FM TUESDAY MORNING. THESE WINDS PERSIST INTO WEDNESDAY
MORNING AFTER WHICH THEY WEAKEN THROUGH THE AFTERNOON AND BEGIN MIGRATING
W AS LIGHTER WINDS SPREAD IN FM THE S-W. ALL WINDS TURN LIGHT OVERNIGHT TO
THURSDAY. THROUGH THURSDAY MORNING STRG TO NEAR GALE WINDS SPREAD S-WWARDS
INTO AREAS N OF 56 N AND W OF 05 W
